CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 24, 1958, pg. A16 reads: "Family Life Conference, sponsored by the Observatory Unit of the Urban League and a number of community groups, was held at Brown Chapel AME Church, North Side, May 17. Panel discussions, workshops including a "Preparation for Marriage" were included in the day's program.  Participating were those in above photo: Edward King, housing specialist; James Traylor, director, Homewood Branch YMCA; MRs .Alberta Nelson, Baxter teacher; Miss Helen Richardson, moderator; Mrs. Virginia Lowe, director of music, Taylor Alderdice High and the Rev. O.L. Simms, minister, Metropolitan Baptist Church. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Edward King, James Traylor, Alberta Nelson, Helen Richardson, Virginia Lowe, and Rev. O.L. Simms, seated in row of wooden high backed chairs in Brown Chapel AME Church for Family Life Conference
